<div class="ornament">· · ·</div>
<article>
<p>This month carries the energy of anticipation — but not the ordinary kind. This is a deeper trembling. A collective holding of breath that goes beyond the personal, beyond the political, into something older and more fundamental.</p>
<p>Many of you feel it without being able to name it. A sense that the world as you have known it is quietly, irreversibly shifting. Not in the way the news describes. Not a crisis that resolves and returns us to normal. Something more permanent than that.</p>
<p>Notice where this lives in your body first. Is there tightness in the chest? A shallowness to your breath? A low hum of vigilance that never fully quiets? That is not anxiety without cause. Your nervous system is responding to something real — a frequency that is moving through all of us right now.</p>
<blockquote>Anticipation is not always fear. It can also be preparation. The question is not how to escape the uncertainty — it is how we choose to meet it.</blockquote>
<p>The structures we built our lives around — financial systems, freedom of movement, the abundance we inherited and rarely questioned — are in motion. We are watching old architectures dissolve and new ones take shape.</p>
<p>The question many are quietly asking — will things go back to normal? — deserves an honest answer: the world that was is not returning. What we are moving into is genuinely new. And within that newness is both loss and possibility.</p>
<p>We begin exactly where we are. We breathe. We release the version of the future that was borrowed from the past. And we ask ourselves the harder, quieter question:</p>
<blockquote>What are you waiting for permission to release?</blockquote>
</article>
